@page "/about"


<PageTitle>About - AtmoSync</PageTitle>


<h2 class="mb-4">ℹ️ About SensorSphere Learning</h2>

<div class="card">
    <div class="card-body">
        <p>
            <strong>SensorSphere Learning</strong> is a small demo IoT Dashboard
            built with <strong>Blazor WebAssembly (.NET 9)</strong>.
        </p>
        <p>
            It uses fake "demo data" for 3 sensors (DHT22, MQ7, MQ136) to teach
            the core building blocks of Blazor:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Components</strong> </li>
            <li><strong>Routing</strong> </li>
            <li><strong>Data Binding</strong> </li>
            <li><strong>Event Handling</strong></li>
            <li><strong>Component Communication</strong> </li>
            <li><strong>Dependency Injection</strong> </li>
            <li><strong>State Management</strong> </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mb-0 text-muted">No backend, no database - everything lives in memory for learning purposes.</p>
    </div>
</div>
